## Interaction Contract

- The root element uses `role="status"`; the visible `text` must describe the state without relying on color.
- Explicit `status` takes precedence over `statusKey`.
- `statusKey` maps `granted → success`, `denied → danger`, `notDetermined → warning`, `unsupported → muted`, and unknown keys to `info`.
- `icon` overrides the resolved tone icon.
- `os` renders a platform icon before the tone icon; `osOnly` hides the tone icon but keeps the text.
- Clicking the badge emits `click` with the original `MouseEvent`.

## API

### Props

| Prop | Type | Default | Description |
|------|------|---------|-------------|
| `text` | `string` | required | Visible badge label. |
| `icon` | `string` | `''` | Custom icon class. Uses the resolved tone icon when omitted. |
| `status` | `'success' \| 'warning' \| 'danger' \| 'info' \| 'muted'` | - | Explicit visual tone. Takes precedence over `statusKey`. |
| `statusKey` | `'granted' \| 'denied' \| 'notDetermined' \| 'unsupported' \| string` | `''` | Permission/status key mapped to a tone. |
| `size` | `'sm' \| 'md'` | `'md'` | Badge density. |
| `os` | `'macos' \| 'windows' \| 'linux'` | - | Optional platform marker icon. |
| `osOnly` | `boolean` | `false` | Render the platform icon but hide the tone icon. |

### Events

| Event | Payload | Description |
|------|---------|-------------|
| `click` | `MouseEvent` | Emitted when the badge root is clicked. |

## Slots

`TxStatusBadge` does not expose slots. Keep the visible status label in `text`; use `icon`, `status`, `statusKey`, and `os` for visual variation.

## Best Practices

- Prefer `statusKey` when the state comes from an API or permission enum; use explicit `status` for page-local decisions.
- Do not use color as the only signal. Keep labels like “Sync healthy” or “Access denied”.
- Use `os` only when the platform materially changes the state being communicated.
- For primary user actions, place a `TxButton` next to the badge instead of making the badge the only control.

